---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Captcha from "../components/Captcha.svelte";
import Svg from "../components/Svg.svelte";
import ProgressWatcher from "../components/ProgressWatcher.svelte";
import ProgressCard from "../components/ProgressCard.svelte";
import dotsBig from "../assets/img/dots-big.png";
---

<Layout>
  <Captcha client:load />

  <section
    class="relative p-2.5 lg:p-5 min-h-[calc(50svh-var(--header-height)-20px)] lg:min-h-[calc(100svh-var(--header-height)-20px)] bg-yellow"
  >
    <Image
      priority
      class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0"
      src={dotsBig}
      alt=""
    />
    <div
      class="absolute max-lg:w-1/2 right-2.5 lg:right-5 bottom-2.5 lg:bottom-5"
    >
      <Svg client:load src="/svg/ledger.svg" class="w-full h-full" />
    </div>
    <div class="relative">
      <p class="mb-2.5 lg:mb-5">III - The Ledger</p>
      <h1 class="uppercase text-7xl lg:text-9xl">
        Investing in a
        <br class="max-lg:hidden" />
        rebel alliance
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="p-2.5 lg:p-5 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:col-start-2 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
        <p>
          These principles light the way towards a different economic model for
          tech: values-driven innovation creating a sustainable business, which
          allows us to reinvest in a movement for an open web. Mozilla’s current
          strategy is built around an explicit double bottom line framework:
        </p>
        <Svg client:load src="/svg/users.svg" class="w-full mb-2.5 lg:mb-5" />
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Mission Impact:</strong> By the end of 2028, 100% of our operating
            organizations will have flagship AI offerings that actively advance the
            Mozilla Manifesto. We're not just building products—we're building proof
            that our principles work at scale.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Market Success:</strong> We're targeting 20% year-over-year growth
            in non-search revenue across our portfolio, with at least three Mozilla
            organizations achieving $25M+ in annual revenue. This isn't growth for
            growth's sake—it's about resilience for this new era.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div
      class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 max-lg:divide-y lg:divide-x divide-dashed bg-yellow"
    >
      <div class="p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">1.4b</p>
        <p>in reserves</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">$620m</p>
        <p>asset growth since 2020</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">$XXX</p>
        <p>approx investments in AI development</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="p-2.5 lg:p-5 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:col-start-2 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
        <p>
          Every org in the Mozilla portfolio — companies and nonprofits — has
          organized its strategy around this double bottom line, ensuring
          everything we do balances mission <em>and</em> money.
        </p>
        <p>
          This has meant continued growth and diversification across Mozilla’s
          portfolio, as Mozilla scales our investments and backs up our
          commitment to do for AI what we did for the web.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div
      class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 max-lg:divide-y lg:divide-x divide-dashed bg-yellow"
    >
      <div class="p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">200m</p>
        <p>approx monthly average Firefox users</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">20m</p>
        <p>approx monthly average Thunderbird users</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="p-2.5 lg:p-5 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:col-start-2 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
        <p>
          We can’t do this alone. But Mozilla, as we enter this next era, is
          building and funding efforts that push AI towards agency and choice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-0">
    <div
      class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:divide-x divide-y divide-dashed bg-yellow"
    >
      <div class="p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">$236m</p>
        <p>investment in philanthropic programs</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">$35m</p>
        <p>investment in Mozilla Ventures Round One</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 p-5 lg:p-10 space-y-2.5">
        <p class="text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase">
          425 grantees and fellows in 46 different countriessince 2020
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ProgressWatcher
    client:load
    current="ledger"
    number="three"
    position="third"
    next="tools"
    text=""
  />

  <ProgressCard client:load full={false} />
</Layout>
